Class BookAndQuillBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dumbdogdiner.stickyapi.bukkit.item.BookAndQuillBuilder
  • public class BookAndQuillBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows for easy construction of a writable book, which is unfortunately much simpler than a written/signed book, either manually in code, or by loading a JSON object

      • fromJson

        @NotNull
public static @NotNull BookAndQuillBuilder fromJson​(@NotNull
                                                    @NotNull com.google.gson.JsonObject bookObject)
        Creates a new BookGenerator from a given JsonObject, representing a book, which can be obtained in whatever way you want.
        Parameters:
        bookObject - A JSON object containing a JsonArray of valid Pages; If a Material.WRITTEN_BOOK is desired, it must contain a title, author, and optionally, a Generation (an integer with the value of 0, 1, 2, or 3, with 0 being the default)
        Returns:
        a BookAndQuillBuilder with the specified pages; if a title and author are both specified, it will be a Material.WRITTEN_BOOK, otherwise it will be a Material.WRITABLE_BOOK
